<subSubSection id="1816497008FC61F349405A24C6978D2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="typification">
<paragraph id="A0DAB3C1EA592E34FDB70EB9CB3A746D" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F7DB158E104B64B9565BBC97B73E92D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Chile • Parque Nacional Vicente Perez 
<taxonomicName id="39508EF713828B9E35B32D49309CFD79" authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Rosales</taxonomicName>
, Volcan Osorno, on the road to the ski area just above Mirador el Bosque, 
<taxonomicName id="6B43B836E9CCABCFB293ED7CE732D285" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Nothofagus dombeyi" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dombeyi">
<emphasis id="58D7C0EC604EF554E4F80BD942974C4C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Nothofagus dombeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest; -41.1382, 72.5370; Matthew Smith and Alija Mujic (MES2942) leg.; 17 April 2017; SGO - 
<emphasis id="204D472BA4773587B1DDE2076893DD89" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">holotype</emphasis>
; FLAS-F-65492 - 
<emphasis id="E515C47531D0B46BCB0810A4A954E4F0" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">isotype</emphasis>
; PDD 116649 - 
<emphasis id="529C826E233E679788506CCD7D3D9571" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">isotype</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="54F75EB1DB830657401465EEABA79599" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="98CE95DF604C5E9AEB09393DF67D0DE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A4267DC1752A87CE2EDADCB34D2B1AB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Refers to the type locality, Volcan Osorno.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8986D5D1CDDCA17951093893D67E7819" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1CF37D8CD7D6D78A26F1ABBB001EB7DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="515B29BE390012A45D63F1E22499D5AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Phylogenetically distinct from other known 
<taxonomicName id="9E370A477888F9E16BF32133C0D94759" authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B338782F78E05BDA3ACF51563442FD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., apothecia 3-6 
<normalizedToken id="7C3D7822CD227ECAFB7AA8ACC0826B72" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2.5 mm, paraphyses taper slightly to rounded apex, ascospores 6.5-10(-11) 
<normalizedToken id="AD1AD7CA7BB0D184FAE774CFCDFF120D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 
<normalizedToken id="EF87C46BC6EA68BE62617864E883449F" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(average 8.3 
<normalizedToken id="3CFE2178BD9EE2805FC69F33A81FFD52" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 
<normalizedToken id="5704212AF030FB3E2BAE0245E95EE266" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EB715D12298A95D3A029A3D2FC1FA69" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="41D44AA3A63B61035A993F038B99126F" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B44D8666F865D312550724DB5E09100A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Apothecia 3-6 mm high, stipe 0.5-1 mm wide, cap 1-2.5 mm wide, the more or less globose cap comprising several closely packed apothecial cups, these arising from short, branches at the top of the stipe, hymenium pale yellow, hymenial areas broken into smaller segments by groups of bright yellow, hair-like elements amongst the fertile parts of the hymenium. Receptacle densely covered with stiff, bright yellow hairs, stipe with shorter hairs. Hairs 50-85 
<normalizedToken id="377C06F463247DB0F7DCAB250F898B22" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 
<normalizedToken id="819FE280583B226EED9C3560897CFDC6" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, straight, with a broad basal cell then cylindric, apically tapering suddenly to the narrow-rounded apex, thin-walled, sparsely septate, densely encrusted with coarse, bright yellow crystals that dissolve in KOH + Melzers. In squash mount, excipular cells broad-cylindric, about 15-30 
<normalizedToken id="FFD394E4D638288E6CADC18E925D3A63" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-12 
<normalizedToken id="A5252F03EBCF8FE38958FE873FD379CA" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, wall slightly thickened, hyaline. Paraphyses 2-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="FB29DD6E0671A4901ECF4699CF7AC2EE" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, tapering slightly to rounded apex, about same length as asci. Asci 40-50 
<normalizedToken id="5F81231959D7FB0CA906EFDDCDBC9C71" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="F65419C3419612D07F97F8052053EB44" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, cylindric, apex rounded, wall thickened, amyloid pore extends through the wall, flaring slightly towards the outside. Ascospores 6.5-10(-11) 
<normalizedToken id="C160CBEFBA16954FF96025363709827B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="DD9281BB8AAF8DE776F08ED3A58B83C5" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(average 8.3 
<normalizedToken id="833207017ED906E74FF9424A31617338" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.0 
<normalizedToken id="071D8688189A2EF8264F6142EF54CC4D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 50), oblong elliptic, ends rounded, one side flat in side view, sometimes slightly curved, 0-septate, hyaline.
</paragraph>
<caption id="923E2CB3F36C3B5AF0839BD11A2700EE" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.80.64435.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540236" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="70D5B0EE55423FDC8CEB6A0A6CB62046" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="20C40CDBB633F320A420B1162731D7E1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Figure 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="29286FB6E54C3DA78F047CF4FE1CBD67" authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus osornoensis" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="osornoensis">
<emphasis id="1A805D165D3A7DBD34058AE73C9B826A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus osornoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(PDD 116649) 
<emphasis id="41F314DD93C836F2FABECD9509C48C9E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A</emphasis>
fresh apothecia (dried apothecia inset) 
<emphasis id="9A376E11BD3C15A648EB8EE73DD7CCDE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B</emphasis>
squash mount, excipulum and hairs in 3% KOH + 
<normalizedToken id="C59693347AB089612F2DA7C063E3F944" originalValue="Melzer’s">Melzer's</normalizedToken>
reagent 
<emphasis id="090FADFDE0EAE6A5F57DB75CC4F9F5AB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C</emphasis>
squash mount, hairs in water showing encrusting crystals 
<emphasis id="641C23C2D33058D3094B2DDDD31AAC06" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">D</emphasis>
paraphyses and asci 
<emphasis id="4557BD5326B8BB2FFC574D222F73D463" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">E</emphasis>
ascospores. Scale bars: 1 mm (
<emphasis id="16122EBE33691B20C57A9D7F66A62EA5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A</emphasis>
); 10 
<normalizedToken id="91A85D7BE523B2FA99D3C223BA8FC94E" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="5FC67434496486EC205269D12B070B05" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B-E</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="233F3FDA666FAEC8F2459622EEBB3128" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A910499C608D26624D8E97E0E3634DB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F86A446E5CA937D9AF9DD0C0737E9E27" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The two Chilean species differ macroscopically, 
<taxonomicName id="64EA6954E3D30EE2F58D6462F2E429CD" authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus osornoensis" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="osornoensis">
<emphasis id="E3C571CA9499907DBE47D6B0F9BA1DC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus osornoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having noticeably broader stipes than 
<taxonomicName id="9968A03D11BF0DBC570887AFA5CBE292" genus="B." lsidName="B. magellanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis id="17E92ED163AD91FADDA6BD8F8EF13830" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and slightly longer ascospores. 
<taxonomicName id="7DFCFDC764F6858CFE50E4C57E876B30" genus="B." lsidName="B. osornoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="osornoensis">
<emphasis id="8A718EF67CDA626E3656543C7060925A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. osornoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<taxonomicName id="26C0F585E2459AE6FCB730DEAFE9DDE2" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Nothofagus dombeyi" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dombeyi">
<emphasis id="4CA84D7F30E6BEDD399C485756283E47" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Nothofagus dombeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest in northern Patagonia on Volcan Osorno in the Vicente Perez 
<taxonomicName id="E37EFE48619274CD2ADC95EDE6673116" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Rosales</taxonomicName>
National Park. It is possible that this 
<taxonomicName id="FF31EEDD27FD20E1663F4B564B9235B0" authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9325F97E364E2129956EBBE8EBD545D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is restricted to the wetter and warmer forests in northern Patagonia, but more specimens are needed to determine the range of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
